OBJECTIVES: To report the results of neoadjuvant chemotherapy (NACT) and the 
impact of interval debulking surgery (IDS) on clinical outcomes of patients 
considered unresectable at primary surgery.
METHODS: Retrospective analysis was carried out on 73 consecutive stage IIIc 
