of survival outcomes in a high percentage of chemoresponsive IIIc ovarian cancer 
patients classified as unresectable at primary surgery. These results are in 
fact inferior to those achievable with optimal primary cytoreduction; however, 
they were quite similar to those seen with suboptimal primary cytoreduction.

